###### Definition 6.2.

The functional \mathcal{J} defined on E satisfies the (S)-property if \{u\_{n}\}\_{n\in\mathbb{N}}
is a sequence in E such that u\_{n}\rightharpoonup u weakly in E and \langle\mathcal{J}^{\prime}(u\_{n}),u\_{n}-u\rangle\to 0, then u\_{n}\to u strongly in E.

The following result characterizes the (S)-property. See [19, Proposition 1.3].

###### Proposition 6.3.

Let E be a uniformly convex Banach space and let A\_{p}\in C^{1}(E,\mathbb{R}) be such that

* (i)

  \langle A\_{p}(u),v\rangle\leq r\|u\|\_{E}^{p-1}\|v\|\_{E}
* (ii)

  \langle A\_{p}(u),u\rangle=r\|u\|^{p}\_{E}

for some r>0, for all u,v\in E. Then A\_{p} satisfies the (S)-property.

